e Rubber Manufacturer Dies Here at 28,'' The New York Times, December 2, 1943, p.27</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==Sources==\n* {{FJC Bio|578|nid=1379846|name=John Warren Davis<!--(1867\u20131945)-->}}\n\n{{s-start}}\n{{s-legal}}\n{{s-bef|before=Seat established by 39 Stat. 48}}\n{{s-ttl|title={{nowrap|Judge of the [[United States District Court for the District of New Jersey]]}}|years=1916\u20131920}}\n{{s-aft|after=[[Joseph Lamb Bodine]]}}\n{{s-bef|before=[[Thomas Griffith Haight]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title={{nowrap|Judge of the [[United States Court of Appeals for the Third Circuit]]}}|years=1920\u20131939}}\n{{s-aft|after=[[Charles Alvin Jones]]}}\n{{s-end}}\n\n{{USAttNJ}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Davis, John Warren}}\n[[Category:1867 births]]\n[[Category:1945 deaths]]\n[[Category:Bucknell University alumni]]\n[[Category:Crozer Theological Seminary alumni]]\n[[Category:Judges of the United States Court of Appeals for the Third Circuit]]\n[[Category:Judges of the United States District Court for the District of New Jersey]]\n[[Category:New Jersey state senators]]\n[[Category:United States Attorneys for the District of New Jersey]]\n[[Category:University of Chicago alumni]]\n[[Category:Leipzig University alumni]]\n[[Category:University of Pennsylvania Law School alumni]]\n[[Category:United States court of appeals judges appointed by Woodrow Wilson]]\n[[Category:20th-century American judges]]\n[[Category:United States district court judges appointed by Woodrow Wilson]]\n[[Category:People from Elizabeth City, North Carolina]]\n", "name_user": "West Virginian", "label": "safe", "comment": "added {{other people|John Warren Davis}}", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/John_Warren_Davis_(judge)"}
